If we make any future modification to a vendored skill (e.g. fix a bug, adapt
to a different runtime), we will:
1. Mark the modified file with a header noting the change
2. Submit the change upstream to Anthropic claude-plugins-official
3. Update VERSIONS.lock to reflect the change

================================================================================
Reverse attribution to upstream
================================================================================

This vendoring exists so that users of code-skills can compose these skills
with the rest of the repository even when Cowork is not installed locally.
All quality, depth, and design credit belongs to the original authors.

If you find a bug or improvement opportunity in a vendored skill, the canonical
fix path is:
  Anthropic / Apollo / Tribe AI / Common Room / Salesforce upstream → vendor sync

We will not silently fork divergent versions.
